'''Day to Praise''' ({{lang-he|יום הלל|yom hallel}}) is a global [[interfaith]] praise initiative set forth by [[Center for Jewish-Christian Understanding and Cooperation|CJCUC]] Chancellor & Founder, [[Shlomo Riskin|Rabbi Shlomo Riskin]] and CJCUC Executive Director, [[David Nekrutman]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.christiannewswire.com/news/3821175639.html|title=Rabbi Riskin Launches 'Day to Praise' Initiative|date=3 March 2015|accessdate=20 March 2015|publisher=Christian Newswire}}</ref> The initiative takes to form in an annual event on [[Yom Ha'atzmaut]] (Israel's Independence Day) in which Christians worldwide are called on and invited<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingisraelnews.com/33579/day-to-praise-calls-christians-jews-worldwide-unite-prayer-biblical-zionism/|title="Day to Praise" Calls on Christians, Jews Worldwide to Unite in Prayer|first=Raphael|last=Poch|publisher=Breaking Israel News|date=23 March 2015|accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref> by Rabbi Riskin to recite [[Hallel]] ([[Psalms]] 113–118) with the [[Jewish]] People in a celebration to praise God for the State of Israel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingisraelnews.com/33498/calling-on-christians-and-jews-to-recite-hallel-on-israeli-independence-day-israel-radio/|title=Calling on Christians and Jews to Recite 'Hallel' on Israeli Independence Day|publisher=Breaking Israel News|date=22 March 2015|accessdate=22 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.charismanews.com/opinion/standing-with-israel/48788-a-day-to-praise-join-israel-in-thanking-god-for-his-continuous-protection|title=A Day to Praise: Join Israel in Thanking God For His Continuous Protection|first=David|last=Nekrutman|publisher=[[Charisma (magazine)|Charisma Magazine]]|date=23 March 2015|accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.cbn.com/jerusalemdateline/archive/2015/03/23/day-of-praise-initiative.aspx|title=Day to Praise Initiative|first=Chris|last=Mitchell|publisher=[[Christian Broadcasting Network|CBN News]]|date=23 March 2015|accessdate=23 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bridgesforpeace.com/il/news/article/initiative-unites-christians-and-jews-to-praise-god-for-the-miracle-of-isra |title=Initiative Unites Christians and Jews to Praise God for the Miracle of Israel |first=Ilse |last=Posselt |publisher=Bridges for Peace |date=24 March 2015 |accessdate=24 March 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150327024341/http://www.bridgesforpeace.com/il/news/article/initiative-unites-christians-and-jews-to-praise-god-for-the-miracle-of-isra |archivedate=27 March 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://jerusalemchannel.tv/historic-day-praise-calls-christians-jews-worldwide-unite-prayer/|title=THIS IS HISTORIC! "Day to Praise" Calls on Christians & Jews Worldwide to Unite in Prayer|first=Christine|last=Darg|publisher=Jerusalem Channel|date=29 March 2015|accessdate=29 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.voiceofisrael.com/the-difference-between-prayer-and-praise/?auto=1|title=The Difference between Prayer and Praise|publisher=[[Voice of Israel]]|date=24 March 2015|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|language=zh |url=http://www.krtnews.com.tw/world/item/15614-%E4%BB%A5%E8%89%B2%E5%88%97%E7%8D%A8%E7%AB%8B%E6%97%A5-%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E7%8C%B6%E5%9F%BA%E8%A6%81%E9%BD%8A%E8%AE%9A%E7%BE%8E%E7%A5%9E |title=以色列獨立日 全球猶基要齊讚美神 |publisher=Kingdom Revival Times |date=25 March 2015 |accessdate=7 April 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721140706/http://www.krtnews.com.tw/world/item/15614-%E4%BB%A5%E8%89%B2%E5%88%97%E7%8D%A8%E7%AB%8B%E6%97%A5-%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E7%8C%B6%E5%9F%BA%E8%A6%81%E9%BD%8A%E8%AE%9A%E7%BE%8E%E7%A5%9E |archivedate=21 July 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingchristiannews.com/articles/display_art.html?ID=15749|title=INSPIRED BY PSALM 117: "DAY TO PRAISE" CALLS ON CHRISTIANS AND JEWS TO THANK GOD FOR ISRAEL'S PROTECTION|first=Raphael|last=Poch|publisher=Breaking Christian News|date=8 April 2015|accessdate=17 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://tconews.com/inspired-by-psalm-117-day-to-praise-calls-on-christians-and-jews-to-thank-god-for-israels-protection/|title=Inspired by Psalm 117: "Day to Praise" Calls on Christians and Jews to Thank God for Israel's Protection|publisher=The Christian Observer|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=17 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |language=zh|url=http://www.taiwanbible.com/web/main/blogView.jsp?ID=157315|title=以色列獨立日 全球猶太人基督徒要齊聲讚美神|publisher=TaiwanBible.com|date=5 April 2015|accessdate=18 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingisraelnews.com/36676/praise-hashem-all-nations-opinion/|title=Praise Hashem All Nations|first=Rabbi Pesach|last=Wolicki|publisher=Breaking Israel News|date=19 April 2015|accessdate=20 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingisraelnews.com/36868/realization-biblical-prophecy-gods-promise-life-israel-biblical-zionism/|title=Realization of Biblical Prophecy, God's Promise Coming to Life in Israel|first=Tuly|last=Weisz|publisher=Breaking Israel News|date=20 April 2015|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>
==Background== [[Hallel]] consists of six [[Psalms]] (113–118), which are recited as a unit, on joyous occasions.<ref>[http://www.ou.org/chagim/hallel.htm Hallel – "Praise of G-d" – OU.ORG]</ref> These occasions include the following: The three pilgrim festivals [[Passover]], [[Shavuot]], and [[Sukkot]] (the "bigger" Jewish holy days, mentioned in the [[Torah]]) and [[Hanukkah]] and [[Rosh Chodesh]] (beginnings of the new month). Two years after the establishment of the State of Israel in 1948, the Chief Rabbinate in Israel decided that [[Yom Ha'atzmaut]] should be given the status of a minor [[Jewish holiday]] on which [[Hallel]] (Psalms 113–118) be recited. The recitation of the blessing over Hallel was introduced in 1973 by Israeli Chief Rabbi [[Shlomo Goren]].
== History == === Conception === In October 2014, [[Shlomo Riskin|Rabbi Shlomo Riskin]], the Chancellor & Founder of the [[Center for Jewish-Christian Understanding and Cooperation]] (CJCUC), became the first Orthodox rabbi to invite Christian visitors to Israel to participate in a "praise rally" with Jewish interfaith leaders at the Center's headquarters during the holiday of [[Sukkot]] during which [[Hallel]] was recited.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.faithnews.cc/?p=18865|title=Hundreds of Christians Joined Rabbi Riskin to Celebrate Sukkot|publisher=Christian Newswire|date=22 October 2014|accessdate=20 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingisraelnews.com/24645/sukkot-celebration-rabbi-riskin-2014-video/|title=Jews and Christians Celebrate Sukkot|publisher=Breaking Israel News|date=7 November 2014|accessdate=20 March 2015}}</ref> This celebratory event would serve as the basis for the eventual conception of the global Day to Praise initiative.
=== In 2015 === [[File:Day to Praise Jerusalem 2015.jpg|thumb|260px|The central Day to Praise event at HaZvi Israel Synagogue in [[Jerusalem]], 23 April 2015]] The Day to Praise Global initiative was launched in March 2015. In an email sent out to Israel supporters worldwide [[Shlomo Riskin|Rabbi Riskin]] wrote:<ref name="rabbi-riskin-email-11-march-2015">{{cite web |url=http://us3.campaign-archive1.com/?u=68fbc11d9f14b345f72e71461&id=2c206aff91|title=A personal invite from Rabbi Shlomo Riskin|publisher=Mailchimp|date=11 March 2015|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref> {{quote|Given the honorary title of Ambassador for Jewish-Christian Relations from Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, God has recently put on my heart to fulfill the mandate of Psalm 117: "Praise the Lord, all you nations; extol him, all you peoples. For great is His love toward us, and the faithfulness of the Lord endures forever." I see the fulfillment of this calling through the nations around the world, who believe in the God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, to recite Psalms 113–118 on Israel's Independence Day with the Jewish community. Therefore, I've recently launched the Day to Praise initiative inviting the Christian world to recite Psalms 113–118 with us.|author=Rabbi [[Shlomo Riskin]]|source=in an email sent out to Israel supporters world-wide, 11 March 2015<ref name="rabbi-riskin-email-11-march-2015" />}}
As part of the praise worship celebrations, Day to Praise produced songs, inspired by the [[Hallel]] Psalms. A portion of the proceeds from these songs go to supporting Heart to Heart, a virtual blood donation program in Israel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingisraelnews.com/36200/not-all-days-to-praise-god-are-created-equal-opinion/|title=Not All Days to Praise God are Created Equal|first=Jonathan|last=Feldstein|publisher=Breaking Israel News|date=15 April 2015|accessdate=17 April 2015}}</ref>
The initiative caused an uproar within the [[Haredi Judaism|Haredi]] Jewish circles. In a statement, the once chief [[List of Sephardi chief rabbis of the Land of Israel|Sephardi Rabbi of Israel]], and the chief Rabbi of Jerusalem, Rabbi [[Shlomo Amar]], expressed his "stomach churning" in light of the joint [[Hallel]] prayer of Jews and Christians in a synagogue in [[Jerusalem]] being led by Rabbi [[Shlomo Riskin]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kikar.co.il/169137.html|title=זעזוע בירושלים: "תפילה" משותפת ליהודים ונוצרים|first=Ishay|last=Cohen|publisher=[[Kikar HaShabbat (website)|Kikar HaShabbat]]|date=22 April 2015|accessdate=23 April 2015}}</ref> In a rebuttal, Rabbi Riskin defended his actions stating, "We are talking about a thanksgiving prayer to G-d that would include Christians who worship His actions towards the Jewish people and the Land of Israel ... What could possibly be more appropriate?".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.israelnationalnews.com/News/News.aspx/194439|title=Rabbi Riskin Defends Jewish-Christian Independence Day Prayer|first=Matt|last=Wanderman|publisher=[[Arutz Sheva]]|date=22 April 2015|accessdate=23 April 2015}}</ref> Later that year, in September, on the eve of [[Rosh HaShana]] (The beginning of the Jewish New Year), Riskin's claim was given further backing by [[Pesach Wolicki|Rabbi Pesach Wolicki]]. In an article written for [[The Times of Israel]], Wolicki wrote, "While discomfort is understandable, we dare not assume that what is uncomfortable and new is therefore forbidden."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.timesofisrael.com/when-interfaith-prayer-is-not-a-foreign-fire/|title=When Interfaith Prayer Is NOT a "Foreign Fire"|first=Pesach|last=Wolicki|publisher=[[The Times of Israel]]|date=13 September 2015|accessdate=15 September 2015}}</ref>
The first annual Day to Praise took place on 23 April 2015 with the central event taking place at HaZvi Israel Synagogue in [[Jerusalem]]. The central Day to Praise event was reportedly joined by tens of thousands of worshipers throughout the world, in their own respective groups.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mariettachurchofgod.org/day-of-praise/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150424043443/http://mariettachurchofgod.org/day-of-praise/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=24 April 2015 |title=DAY OF PRAISE |publisher=Marietta Church of God (Georgia) |date=17 April 2015 |accessdate=24 April 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wherevent.com/detail/The-Liberty-University-Day-to-Praise%282%29|title=Day to Praise|publisher=[[Liberty University]] (Virginia)|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/ElShaddaiMinist/status/591276189924360192|title=Day to Praise|publisher=El Shaddai Ministries (Washington State)|date=23 April 2015|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://jerusalemchannel.tv/historic/|title=Historic 'Day to Praise' Includes Christians on Israeli Independence Day|first=Christine|last=Darg|publisher=Jerusalem Channel|date=24 April 2015|accessdate=25 April 2015}}</ref>
Later that year, in 2015, during the festival of [[Sukkot]], CJCUC, together with its founder, Rabbi [[Shlomo Riskin]], the chief rabbi of [[Efrat]], hosted an interfaith event in Efrat in which 200 Christians and Jews came together to sing the praises of God in unity. Riskin said that the event would help usher in the [[Messianic Age]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.breakingisraelnews.com/51082/rabbi-shlomo-riskin-interfaith-prayer-bringing-us-closer-to-messianic-age-biblical-zionism/|title=Rabbi Shlomo Riskin: Interfaith Prayer "Bringing Us Closer" to Messianic Age|first= Adam Eliyahu|last=Berkowitz|publisher=Breaking Israel News|date=14 October 2015|accessdate=15 October 2015}}</ref>
===In 2016=== The second annual Day to Praise took place on 12 May 2016 and the central event was held in [[Gush Etzion]], the scene of many past terror attacks. The event consisted of 120 representatives of the [[Jewish]] and Christian faiths. The representatives were groups from Israel, The United States, Germany and Brazil and international interfaith organizations such as "Bridges for Peace" and "Christian Friends of Israel".<ref name="TOI2016">{{cite web|url=http://www.breakingisraelnews.com/67654/christians-jews-coming-together-fulfill-prophecies/|title=WATCH: Miracle of Modern Israel Brings Jews and Christians Together in Prophetic Gathering|first=Adam Eliyahu|last=Berkowitz|website=Breaking Israel News|date=15 May 2016|access-date=15 May 2016}}</ref>
During the event, each of the participants read [[Psalm 117]] in their native language, and then read it together in [[Hebrew]]. According to co-founder [[David Nekrutman]], this in-gathering was the fulfilment of the [[biblical prophecy]] of [[Zephaniah]]: "For then will I turn to the peoples a pure language that they may all call upon the name of the LORD to serve Him with one consent." ({{Bibleverse|Zephaniah|3:9|KJV}})<ref name="TOI2016" /><ref name="BFP2016">{{cite web |url=http://www.bridgesforpeace.com/il/news/article/day-to-praise-jews-christians-unite-to-praise-god-for-the-miracle-of-i |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160608080805/http://www.bridgesforpeace.com/il/news/article/day-to-praise-jews-christians-unite-to-praise-god-for-the-miracle-of-i |dead-url=yes |archive-date=8 June 2016 |title="Day to Praise" – Jews, Christians Unite to Praise God for the Miracle of Israel |first=Ilse |last=Posselt |website=Bridges for Peace |date=16 May 2016 |access-date=16 May 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref name="PAD2016">{{cite web|language=es|url=http://www.profeciaaldia.com/2016/05/day-to-praise-hallel-rabinos-israel-y-cristianos-del-mundo-independecia-israel-cumplimiento-profetico-sofonias-3.9.html|title=Rabinos de Israel y Cristianos de todo el mundo se unen cumpliendo Sofonías 3:9 (Vídeo)|first=Roger|last=Casco Herrera|website=Profecía Al Día|date=19 May 2016|access-date=20 May 2016}}</ref>
