{{Infobox wildfire |title=Natchez Fire | image = 2018 07 20-17.35.58.042-CDT.jpg | caption = Natchez Fire on July 20, 2018 | reference= <ref name="Natchez Fire" /> | cost=Unknown | date={{Start date|2018|7|15}} – {{End date|2018|10|30}} | location=[[Siskiyou County, California|Siskiyou County]], [[California]], [[United States]], near the California–Oregon Border | coordinates={{coord|41.956|-123.551|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map=USA California | pushpin_map_caption=Location of fire in California | area={{convert|38,134|acre|km2|0}} | injuries=None reported | fatalities=None reported | cause=[[Lightning]] | landuse= | perps= | motive= }} The '''Natchez Fire''' was a wildfire that burned near the California and Oregon Border in [[Siskiyou County, California|Siskiyou County]], [[California]], in the United States. The Natchez Fire began on July 15, 2018, due to lightning,<ref name="Natchez Fire">{{Cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/5948/|title=Natchez Fire Information - InciWeb the Incident Information System|author=|website=inciweb.nwcg.gov|language=en|date=October 7, 2018|access-date=October 30, 2018}}</ref> and the fire burned a total of {{convert|38,134|acre|km2 sqmi|0}} before it was fully contained on October 30, 2018.<ref name="Natchez Fire2" />
==Timeline== The Natchez Fire ignited 8 miles north of Happy Camp on July 15, 2018, around 6:30 P.M. PDT, due to lightning.<ref name="Natchez Fire" /> During the next couple of weeks, the Natchez Fire gradually expanded in size, reaching {{convert|6,174|acres|km2}} by July 31, with 15% containment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/44716/|title=Natchez Fire Update – 7/31/2018|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=July 31, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref>
The fire continued to burn into the month of August, while continuing to grow. On August 11, 2018, the fire had burned a total of {{convert|12,449|acres|km2}} and was 52% contained.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/45586/|title=Natchez Fire Update – 8/11/2018|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=August 11, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> By August 14, 2018, the fire had burned a total of {{convert|15,940|acres|km2}} and was 55% contained.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/45898/|title=Natchez Fire Update – 8/15/2018|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=August 15, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> The fire continued to grow in size during the next couple of weeks. On August 31, the Natchez Fire had burned {{convert|27,076|acres|km2}} and was 70% contained.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/47213/|title=Natchez Fire Update – 8/31/2018|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=August 31, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref>
During the first week of September, the Natchez Fire quickly expanded in size, due to a heat wave and dry conditions, reaching {{convert|31,979|acres|km2}} by September 8, while containment increased only slightly to 74%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/47629/|title=Natchez Fire Update – 9/8/2018|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=September 8, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> Afterward, the Natchez Fire grew at a much slower pace, while firefighters continued making progress on containing the fire. By September 19, the Natchez Fire had reached {{convert|33,340|acres|km2}}, while containment increased to 84%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/48124/|title=Natchez Fire Update – 9/19/2018–9/23/2018|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=September 19, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> On September 25, the Natchez Fire grew to {{convert|35,037|acres|km2}}, while containment dropped to 82%.<ref name="Natchez Fire" /> On September 28, the Natchez Fire had expanded to {{convert|37,193|acres|km2}}, while containment increased to 84%.<ref name="Natchez Fire" /> By October 2, the Natchez Fire had grown to {{convert|38,134|acres|km2}}, while containment remained at 84%.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/48554/|title=Natchez Fire Update for October 2-3|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=October 2, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref> Afterward, the Natchez Fire stopped growing in size while firefighters gradually increased the containment of the wildfire, with containment reaching 89% by October 7.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/article/5948/48627/|title=FINAL Natchez Fire Update - Oct. 7|author=|publisher=InciWeb|date=October 7, 2018|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref> On October 30, 2018, the Natchez Fire was finally 100% contained.<ref name="Natchez Fire2">{{cite web|url=http://www.fire.ca.gov/current_incidents/incidentdetails/Index/2181/|title=Natchez Fire|author=|publisher=[[CAL FIRE]]|date=October 30, 2018|accessdate=November 8, 2018}}</ref>
